Skip malformed PAA certificates fetched from the DCL instead of crashing.

The Matter Distributed Compliance Ledger (DCL) occasionally serves a PAA root
certificate with trailing data after the signature algorithm. Newer
`cryptography` releases (strict, Rust-based ASN.1 parser) raise ValueError on
these. python-matter-server only wraps the DCL fetch in
`except (ClientError, TimeoutError)`, so a single bad cert propagates a
ValueError out of `MatterServer.start()` *before* the WebSocket port is bound,
leaving the systemd service in a restart loop (TCP 5580 never opens).

Guard the parse so a bad cert is skipped and the server keeps starting.
Remove once fixed upstream:
  https://github.com/home-assistant-libs/python-matter-server

--- a/matter_server/server/helpers/paa_certificates.py
+++ b/matter_server/server/helpers/paa_certificates.py
@@ -72,6 +72,12 @@ async def write_paa_root_cert(
             warnings.simplefilter("ignore", CryptographyDeprecationWarning)
 
-        cert = x509.load_pem_x509_certificate(pem_certificate.encode())
+        try:
+            cert = x509.load_pem_x509_certificate(pem_certificate.encode())
+        except ValueError as err:
+            LOGGER.warning(
+                "Skipping unparseable PAA certificate %s: %s", subject, err
+            )
+            return False
 
     ski: x509.SubjectKeyIdentifier = cert.extensions.get_extension_for_class(
         x509.SubjectKeyIdentifier
